# Get the value counts for tier_id
tier_id_counts = df['tier_name'].value_counts().reset_index()
tier_id_counts.columns = ['Tier_Name', 'Count']

# Plotting the value counts for tier_id
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(data=tier_id_counts, x='Tier_Name', y='Count')
plt.title('Value Counts for Tier Name')
plt.xlabel('Tier Name')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

plt.xlabel('Fiscal Week')
plt.ylabel('Sales')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

# 4. Correlation Between Orders and Sales Over Fiscal Weeks
orders_sales_correlation = df.groupby('fiscal_week').apply(lambda x: x['orders'].corr(x['sales'])).reset_index()
orders_sales_correlation.columns = ['fiscal_week', 'correlation']

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(data=orders_sales_correlation, x='fiscal_week', y='correlation')
plt.title('Correlation Between Orders and Sales Over Fiscal Weeks')
plt.xlabel('Fiscal Week')
plt.ylabel('Correlation')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()
In [36]:
# 5. Household Eligibility Over Fiscal Weeks
eligibility_distribution = df.groupby(['fiscal_week', 'hh_eligibility'])['household_id'].count().reset_index()
eligibility_distribution.columns = ['fiscal_week', 'hh_eligibility', 'count']

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.barplot(data=eligibility_distribution, x='fiscal_week', y='count', hue='hh_eligibility')
plt.title('Household Eligibility Over Fiscal Weeks')
plt.xlabel('Fiscal Week')
plt.ylabel('Count')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend(title='Eligibility Status')
plt.show()

# Aggregating data for fiscal week vs orders, items, sales, and profits
fiscal_week_trends = df.groupby('fiscal_week')[['orders', 'items', 'sales', 'profit']].sum().reset_index()

# Plotting fiscal week vs orders, items, sales, and profits
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

sns.lineplot(data=fiscal_week_trends, x='fiscal_week', y='orders', label='Orders', marker='o')
sns.lineplot(data=fiscal_week_trends, x='fiscal_week', y='items', label='Items', marker='o')
sns.lineplot(data=fiscal_week_trends, x='fiscal_week', y='sales', label='Sales', marker='o')
sns.lineplot(data=fiscal_week_trends, x='fiscal_week', y='profit', label='Profit', marker='o')

plt.title('Trend of Orders, Items, Sales, and Profits with respect to Fiscal Weeks')
plt.xlabel('Fiscal Week')
plt.ylabel('Metrics')
plt.legend(title='Metrics')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()
